Yeah, I'm aware of it. But it's not getting worse than it already is. My concern is that subscribe#onComplete gets called before theonNext on the last item with the current implementation. We should make sure onComplete gets called right after the last item gets dispatched. Something like the following:
       if (delivered.incrementAndGet() <= limit) {
            subscriber.onNext(t);

            if (delivered.get() == limit) {
                subscription.cancel();
                subscriber.onComplete();
            }
        }

We should probably just mirror how flowable does it to get it right. I've seen too many race conditions

